    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">strategy...is fun.  this one&#39;s fun to play with some new cards.  i know eowyn isn&#39;t actually out yet, but she&#39;s great at keeping your fellowship large.  heal your guys with elrond, prevent wounds with eowyn and intimidate (enquea? who&#39;s that?) and keep frodo safe with merry, paths, and servant.  big fellowship is the key.  maybe throw in a grimir and a durin&#39;s secret for fun.  saruman and moria have trouble against this &#39;cause of betrayal of isengard killing the old man, and &#39;cause it counteracts armories (which also get canceled or returned to hand with dreary or vilya). shadow side is cool for killing allies, killing exhausted guys, beating people up with nazgul.  good for stopping people early so you can move slow if need be.  if you&#39;re ahead AT ALL and someone puts out 7 companions, their number must be few hits the table and you NEVER need to play minions.  secret sentinels can sit in their hand and never get played.<br />
<br />
it&#39;s not tier 1, but it&#39;s something new and different to play when you&#39;re bored of the same &#39;ol same &#39;ol.<br />
<br />
